Two jumps in a week, I bet you

[Chorus]

Drying up in conversation
You will be the one who cannot talk
All your insides fall to pieces
You just sit there wishing you could still make love
They're the ones who'll hate you
When you think you've got the world all sussed out
They're the ones who'll spit at you
And you'll be the one screaming out

[Chorus]
Don't leave me high
Don't leave me dry
Don't leave me high
Don't leave me dry

[Bridge]
Oh, it's the best thing that you've ever had
The best thing that you've ever, ever had
Yeah, it's the best thing that you've ever had
The best thing you've had has gone away

[Chorus]
Don't leave me high
Don't leave me dry
Don't leave me high
Don't leave me dryYou might also like1Embed

search_results.lyrics:
​when i look at you. Lyrics[Verse 1]
I begged you to stay
As my mind spun around the room that day
But I watched you leave instead
So I spent the day drawing lines in bed
Why'd you have to go?
My mind changes like the tide, I know
And the tide has turned our love
And it's not me you're thinking of

[Chorus 1]
But when I looked at you
When I looked at you
I felt my head come loose
[Verse 2]
Now I couldn't see the signs
That you said were clear, that you said were mine
So you laid them out for me
And I cried so hard that I couldn't breathe
Tonight I'll go to sleep
With another ghost inside of me
And I know you'll forget
What it's like to be stuck in my head

[Chorus 2]
But when I looked at you
When I looked at you
I felt my grip come loose
When I looked at you
When I looked at you
I knew we couldn't undo

[Bridge]
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

[Chorus 3]
When I look at you
When I look at you
I feel my head come loose
When you look at me (Keep on moving further from me)
I know you feel it too (Keep on moving further from me)
There's nothing time can do (Keep on moving further from me)You might also likeEmbed

search_results.title: Black Star
search_results.lyrics:
Black Star Lyrics[Verse 1]
I get home from work
And you're still standing in your dressing gown
Well, what am I to do?
I know all the things around your head
And what they do to you

[Pre-Chorus 1]
What are we coming to?
What are we gonna do?
[Chorus]
Blame it on the black star
Blame it on the falling sky
Blame it on the satellite
That beams me home

[Verse 2]
The troubled words of a troubled mind
I try to understand what is eating you
I try to stay awake, but it's fifty hours
Since that I last slept with you

[Pre-Chorus 2]
What are we coming to?
I just don't know anymore

[Chorus]
Blame it on the black star
Blame it on the falling sky
Blame it on the satellite
That beams me home

[Verse 3]
I get on the train and I just stand about
Now that I don't think of you
I keep falling over, I keep passing out
When I see a face like you
You might also like[Pre-Chorus 3]
What am I coming to?
I'm gonna melt down

[Chorus]
Blame it on the black star
Blame it on the falling sky
Blame it on the satellite
That beams me homeEmbed
